* "sigma algebra" is an algebra of sets which can intersect countable number of subsets
* smallest including sigma algebra
	\ links-to internal eupxeczurplflvll
* the Borel sets are the smallest sigma algebra of sets including the open sets [or all the closed sets]
	* see smallest including sigma algebra
		\ links-to internal eupxeczurplflvll
* definition: the "product" of sigma-algebras is the sigma-algebra generated by their cartesian product
	* product is associative
		* proof
			\ links-to internal iwfenxtlwaiscnnn